deposit_type_candidate.observed_name:
Porphyry gold 

Results: Intermittent cuprite, chalcopyrite,-bornite zone.; notes contained numerous multielement anomalies and geophysical anomalies explained how this could make Northway property in need of follow-up exploration activities.

Porphyry copper-molybdenum 

Results: zones of pyrite, biotite-rich, and molybdenite zone libelle; results were noted during due diligence inspection of high-angle, remobilized structures were noted, invalidating the potential for any follow-up.

Porphyry copper 

Results: Chalcopyrite ± bornite core zone within areas 6 and 7; geologic outcropping compositions supported by mineral assemblages and chargeability anomalies; high-grade ores required excavation during exploration projects.
